{"id": 2528, "source": "pestle", "subject": "physics", "course": null, "level": "SL", "paper": "1", "year": "2018", "session": "18N", "subtopic": "3-2-modelling-a-gas", "title": "18N.1.SL.TZ0.12", "topic_id": "3", "source_url": "https://pestle.pages.dev/app/", "question_html": "<div class=\"question\">\n<p>Container X contains 1.0 mol of an ideal gas. Container Y contains 2.0 mol of the ideal gas. Y has four times the volume of X. The pressure in X is twice that in Y.</p>\n<p>What is <span class=\"mjpage\"><math alttext=\"\\frac{{{\\text{temperature of gas in X}}}}{{{\\text{temperature of gas in Y}}}}\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\">\n<mfrac>\n<mrow>\n<mrow>\n<mtext>temperature of gas in X</mtext>\n</mrow>\n</mrow>\n<mrow>\n<mrow>\n<mtext>temperature of gas in Y</mtext>\n</mrow>\n</mrow>\n</mfrac>\n</math></span>?</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>A.   <span class=\"mjpage\"><math alttext=\"\\frac{1}{4}\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\">\n<mfrac>\n<mn>1</mn>\n<mn>4</mn>\n</mfrac>\n</math></span></p>\n<p>B.   <span class=\"mjpage\"><math alttext=\"\\frac{1}{2}\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\">\n<mfrac>\n<mn>1</mn>\n<mn>2</mn>\n</mfrac>\n</math></span></p>\n<p>C.   1</p>\n<p>D.   2</p>\n</div>", "solution_html": "<div class=\"question\">\n<p>C</p>\n</div>", "examiners_html": "<div class=\"question\">\n[N/A]\n</div>"}